posts.raw_content:
Alright dipshits, this was a bait post to see how many of you anti Israel nuts would take it, and to show those who are just being manipulated; how easy it is to do when youre living in fear. I dont hate Israel at all, nor do I think we should just abandon them to their fate, as as much as some of you think they arent our "friends", true red blooded Americans dont treat OUR friends that way. Being American means standing by your friends, even when you disagree with what they are doing. And despite the lunatic shit people try to pin on the Israelis, they've only ever been in our court. You can have issues with the way specific Israelis behave, but overall they are one of our true allies in a world increasingly bent on its own self interest, not to mention the push towards globalism.

Now some of you will point to people like yuval harari and say "but look at this globalist jew, how can you agree with him?"  Because I dont, and I dont think people like yuval represent the majority of Israeli thinking, let alone the entirety of jews across the world. 

And I ask you who have only been caught up in the zeitgeist to pause and ask yourself why you have decided Israel is behind all the worlds problems? Has it been because you truly believe it to be so, or have others used lies and attacks like the USS liberty to try and paint Israel as backstabbers who will turn on you at a moments notice? What muslim country has been more upfront, and treated America as a partner? Not a perfect one, and not ignoring mutual spying that goes on, but such things are a normal part of statecraft, to act like Israel is a lone evil for doing so is just insanity.

And for those whos position on middle east entanglements stems from a desire to be removed from the worlds affairs, I understand your position entirely and mostly agree with it, but I ask you one question. Is it truly practical to act like you are not part of this world, just because you disagree with the direction its heading? We are part of this world, whether we like it or not. And sometimes, even when we do that, like we did in the beginning of ww2, the world comes to you anyway. Food for thought everyone, and Ill remember all you who turned on Israel over your own fears. But you know who has even better memory than me? God, and the people you malign are His chosen, regardless of the mental gymnastics you engage in to avoid it. Good luck. Genesis 12:3
